If we could go back to the events of 1994,

00:07:10.980 --> 00:07:12.980
when the genocide stopped,

00:07:12.980 --> 00:07:15.980
what happened to our brothers and sisters?

00:07:15.980 --> 00:07:18.980
Something amazing happened.

00:07:18.980 --> 00:07:20.980
You see,

00:07:20.980 --> 00:07:23.980
years before the genocide,

00:07:23.980 --> 00:07:28.980
there were some brothers living outside the country as refugees.

00:07:28.980 --> 00:07:30.980
During the genocide,

00:07:30.980 --> 00:07:33.980
more brothers fled the country.

00:07:33.980 --> 00:07:35.980
So after the genocide,

00:07:35.980 --> 00:07:38.980
the Erdas helped those brothers

00:07:38.980 --> 00:07:40.980
to find their way back home.

00:07:40.980 --> 00:07:43.980
Then after, they started shepherding everyone

00:07:43.980 --> 00:07:45.980
to promote unity.

00:07:45.980 --> 00:07:46.980
How good.

00:07:46.980 --> 00:07:50.980
But if they're all Rwandan brothers and sisters,

00:07:50.980 --> 00:07:53.980
then why were the elders focusing on unity?

00:07:53.980 --> 00:07:56.980
They were strong feelings for those who fled the country

00:07:56.980 --> 00:07:58.980
and those who stayed.

00:07:58.980 --> 00:08:02.980
But the Erdas used Bible accounts

00:08:02.980 --> 00:08:04.980
and the Bible principles

00:08:04.980 --> 00:08:05.980
to help them see

00:08:05.980 --> 00:08:08.980
that freeing was a personal decision.

00:08:08.980 --> 00:08:11.980
And this helped the brothers

00:08:11.980 --> 00:08:13.980
to unite Mokitri.

00:08:13.980 --> 00:08:14.980
I see.

00:08:14.980 --> 00:08:17.980
Again, the power of God working through the elder arrangement

00:08:17.980 --> 00:08:19.980
to unify them.

00:08:19.980 --> 00:08:22.980
And were the results of all that shepherding?

00:08:22.980 --> 00:08:24.980
Yes.

00:08:24.980 --> 00:08:28.980
You see, the genocide was stopped in the dry 1994.

00:08:28.980 --> 00:08:30.980
A few months later,

00:08:30.980 --> 00:08:34.980
